  "body": "@tdickman and I  experiencing unexpected behavior when running `helm install` versus `helm upgrade --install`. \r\nIf I run these while in my `rreackhof` namespace, these are the results:\r\n```console\r\n$ helm install stable/mysql\r\n$ helm ls\r\nNAME                                    REVISION        UPDATED                         STATUS          CHART           NAMESPACE\r\nturbulent-koala                         1               Fri Aug  4 15:22:55 2017        DEPLOYED        mysql-0.2.6     rreackhof\r\n```\r\n```console\r\n$ helm upgrade release-name --install stable/mysql\r\n$ helm ls \r\nNAME                                    REVISION        UPDATED                         STATUS          CHART           NAMESPACE\r\nrelease-name                            1               Fri Aug  4 15:26:18 2017        DEPLOYED        mysql-0.2.6     default\r\n```\r\nPassing `--kube-context` also does not change the results. I believe that `install` and `upgrade --install` should behave the same way.",
